From 41eaeed4d3f3014f4bb1b30eceb759cc0fcc72c1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 08:31:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Lockscreen: render edge-to-edge over systemui bars

Configure the keyguard window for transparent fullscreen rendering
(transparent background, layout-fullscreen, own bars hidden) and let
the Wallpaper Image and outer content Flex expandSafeArea on all
edges. The keyguard is z-order above SystemUi_StatusBar /
SystemUi_NavigationBar, so the lockscreen now paints over them at
y=0 instead of being inset by their safe-area reservation.

Removes the empty StatusBar placeholder column and dead mHeightPx
field; StatusBar now sits at the top of the main content Flex.
Also resets backgroundScale 1.1 -> 1 so the wallpaper isn't cropped
during the unlock animation.

Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Change-Id: I69205e84ea62355601e1310eeb6843d4bbe37a7b
---
